8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
9 Section 1. K.S.A. 21-5801 is hereby amended to read as follows: 21-
10 5801. (a) Theft is any of the following acts done with intent to
11 permanently deprive the owner of the possession, use or benefit of the
12 owner's property or services:
13 (1) Obtaining or exerting unauthorized control over property or
14 services;
15 (2) obtaining control over property or services, by deception;
16 (3) obtaining control over property or services, by threat;
17 (4) obtaining control over stolen property or services knowing, or
18 having reason to know, the property or services to have been were stolen
19 by from another; or
20 (5) knowingly dispensing motor fuel into a storage container or the
21 fuel tank of a motor vehicle at an establishment in which motor fuel is
22 offered for retail sale and leaving the premises of the establishment
23 without making payment for the motor fuel.
24 (b) Theft of:
25 (1) Property or services of the value of $100,000 or more is a severity
26 level 5, nonperson felony;
27 (2) property or services of the value of at least $25,000 but less than
28 $100,000 is a severity level 7, nonperson felony;
29 (3) property or services of the value of at least $1,500 but less than
30 $25,000 is a severity level 9, nonperson felony, except as provided in
31 subsection (b)(7);
32 (4) property or services of the value of less than $1,500 is a class A

