13 (7) property that is a firearm of the value of less than $25,000 is a
14 severity level 9, nonperson felony; and and
15 (8) property that is mail of the value of less than $1,500 from three
16 separate locations within a period of 72 hours as part of the same act or
17 transaction or in two or more acts or transactions connected together or
18 constituting parts of a common scheme or course of conduct is a severity
19 level 9, nonperson felony; and
20 (9) property that is a motor vehicle of the value of less than $1,500 is
21 a severity level 10, nonperson felony; and
22 (9) property that is a motor vehicle of the value of at least $500 but
23 less than $1,500 is a severity level 10, nonperson felony.
24 (c) As used in this section:
25 (1) "Conviction" or "convicted" includes being convicted of a
26 violation of K.S.A. 21-3701, prior to its repeal, this section or a municipal
27 ordinance which prohibits the acts that this section prohibits;
28 (2) "mail" means a letter, postal card, package or bag sent through the
29 United States postal service or other delivery service, or any other article
30 or thing contained therein;
31 (3) "regulated scrap metal" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 2024
32 Supp. 50-6,109, and amendments thereto;
33 (4) "remote service unit" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 9-
34 1111, and amendments thereto, and includes, but is not limited to,
35 automated cash dispensing machines and automated teller machines; and
36 (5) "value" means the value of the property or, if the property is
37 regulated scrap metal or a remote service unit, the cost to restore the site of
38 the theft of such regulated scrap metal or remote service unit to its
39 condition at the time immediately prior to the theft of such regulated scrap
40 metal or remote service unit, whichever is greater.
41 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 21-5801 is hereby repealed.
42 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
43 publication in the statute book.

